subanswer.text:
To find the distance between two points $(x_1, y_1)$ and $(x_2, y_2)$, use the formula $\sqrt{(x_2 - x_1)^2 + (y_2 - y_1)^2}$. Applying this formula to vertices B and E yields:

\begin{align*}
d_{BE} &= \sqrt{(E_x - B_x)^2 + (E_y - B_y)^2} \\
        &= \sqrt{(6 - 4)^2 + (8 - 2)^2} \\
        &\approx \boxed{6.16}
\end{align*}

Therefore, vertices B and E are approximately $\boxed{6.16}$ units apart.

